---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const APP_URL = "https://app.worshipmetrics.com";
const SITE_URL = "https://worshipmetrics.com";
const R2 = "https://pub-a4845709a76642e7943bcb8b80677531.r2.dev/main";
const HERO_IMAGE = `${R2}/homepage/new%20images/Worship%20Volunteers%20Working%20Together.jpg`;
const TEAM_IMAGE = `${R2}/Tech%20Manager/WorshipMetrics%20Tech%20Manager%20Web-UI%20Panels.jpg`;
const INVITE_IMAGE = `${R2}/homepage/Invite%20Team%20Member.jpg`;

const capabilityItems = [
  "Skill tags so production, welcome, and ministry roles are assigned intentionally",
  "Training checklists that make onboarding less dependent on one experienced volunteer",
  "Role clarity that helps people grow into bigger responsibilities over time",
  "A cleaner record of who is ready for what before the schedule gets built",
];

const scheduleItems = [
  "Recurring availability and blackout windows in one place",
  "Assignment workflows tied directly to the service plan",
  "A clearer picture of who is overloaded and who can still step in",
  "Less week-of scrambling and fewer last-minute text threads",
];

const avClubItems = [
  "Teenagers can step into one clear role without learning the whole booth on day one",
  "Older volunteers can mentor newer ones instead of carrying the whole Sunday alone",
  "The team grows from camera operator to director instead of staying stuck at emergency staffing",
  "Youth ministry and production ministry finally have a shared win to point at",
];

const structuredData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "SoftwareApplication",
  name: "WorshipMetrics Volunteers",
  applicationCategory: "BusinessApplication",
  operatingSystem: "Web, iOS, Android",
  url: `${SITE_URL}/volunteers`,
  image: HERO_IMAGE,
  description: "Volunteer capabilities, scheduling, communications, and replacement workflows built into the same system that runs Sunday.",
  offers: {
    "@type": "Offer",
    price: "0",
    priceCurrency: "USD",
    availability: "https://schema.org/InStock",
    url: `${SITE_URL}/pricing`,
  },
};
---

<Layout
  title="Volunteers"
  socialTitle="Worship Metrics Volunteers"
  description="Volunteer capabilities, scheduling, communications, and replacement workflows built into the same system that runs Sunday."
  canonical="/volunteers"
  ogImage={HERO_IMAGE}
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-indigo-50 via-white to-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.95fr)_minmax(0,1.05fr)]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">Volunteers</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          Grow a volunteer team that does not collapse onto one person.
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600 sm:text-xl">
          Worship Metrics helps churches track capabilities, availability, reliability, and communication in the same workflow that builds the service plan. That makes it easier to recruit, train, and keep people serving.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-start gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap sm:items-center">
          <a href={`${APP_URL}/sign-up`} class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
          <a href="/av-club" class="btn-outline">Start an AV Club</a>
          <a href="/services" class="btn-outline">See how it fits Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[1.75rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-[0_24px_60px_rgba(15,23,42,0.12)]">
        <img src={HERO_IMAGE} alt="Volunteers working together with WorshipMetrics" loading="eager" decoding="async" class="aspect-[16/10] w-full object-cover" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,0.92fr)]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">Capabilities and training</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Know who can serve where before the schedule gets stressful.</h2>
        <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3">
          {capabilityItems.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 sm:text-base"><span class="mt-2 h-2.5 w-2.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-indigo-500"></span><span>{item}</span></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
        <img src={INVITE_IMAGE} alt="Volunteer capability and invitation workflow in WorshipMetrics" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aspect-[16/10] w-full object-cover" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-50 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.95fr)_minmax(0,1.05fr)]">
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-3xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
        <img src={TEAM_IMAGE} alt="Volunteer-friendly control panels in WorshipMetrics" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aspect-[16/10] w-full object-cover" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">Availability and scheduling</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Build the team with real availability, not guesses.</h2>
        <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3">
          {scheduleItems.map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-slate-700 sm:text-base"><span class="mt-2 h-2.5 w-2.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-indigo-500"></span><span>{item}</span></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl rounded-[2rem] border border-indigo-100 bg-indigo-50 p-8 shadow-sm sm:p-12">
      <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,0.9fr)]">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">AV Club strategy</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">This is how you turn willing teenagers into a real ministry team.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-600 sm:text-lg">
            Churches do not just need more volunteers. They need a better way to bring people in, especially younger people who want to help but do not know where they fit yet. That is where an AV Club becomes powerful.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {avClubItems.map((item) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white bg-white p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-700 shadow-sm">{item}</div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-start gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
        <a href="/av-club" class="btn-primary">See how to start an AV Club</a>
        <a href="/av-team" class="btn-outline">See the seven team roles</a>
        <a href="/pricing" class="btn-outline">See plans</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-950 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl rounded-[2rem] border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-8 shadow-2xl sm:p-12">
      <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,0.95fr)]">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-300">How it connects to Services</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">Volunteer management is not a side tool. It is how Sunday becomes shareable.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-300 sm:text-lg">
            The moment a church starts planning services more intentionally, the people layer matters just as much as the item list. Volunteers exists to make that handoff smoother and to make growth possible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            "Positions in the service plan connect directly to real people instead of placeholders.",
            "The booth, the welcome team, and ministry leaders can work from the same picture of Sunday.",
            "Scheduling decisions improve because the service workflow and volunteer workflow stop living in separate systems.",
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-200">{item}</div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-start gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center">
        <a href="/services" class="btn-primary">See Services</a>
        <a href="/av-club" class="btn-outline" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);color:#fff;">Build an AV Club</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Give your team a better way to show up.</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-600 sm:text-lg">
        Start with the Free Forever workflow, then connect capabilities, scheduling, and service-day assignments in one system that can support the whole ministry.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap">
        <a href={`${APP_URL}/sign-up`} class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
        <a href="/av-club" class="btn-outline">Start an AV Club</a>
        <a href="/pricing" class="btn-outline">Compare plans</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
